post_text: Entrepreneurship students "Think Outside the Box." Each of the five groups had a baggie with puzzle pieces. They had 20 minutes to put their puzzles together without any specific instructions. They quickly realized that each bag had a mixture of puzzles, and they had three choices to solve their problem - complain about it, quit, or take responsibility to solve the problem. The groups learned they needed to negotiate terms in order to come up with a solution. Some entrepreneurial foundational values they learned are: knowledge, sound judgement, responsibility, win-win focus, freedom, opportunity mindset, and comparative advantage.

We'll find out more about what Colby Barradas scored in NSDA Dramatic Interpretation when the nationals tournament is done, but unfortunately, he didn't make it on to the Top 30. He and I both agreed that the competition was particularly tough the last round, but it's amazing that this young actor was able to get to the top 60 in the United States. We're proud of you, Colby Barradas!

PS. Special thanks to Scott Powell for helping us figure out tech and spending hours to do so; for Molly Swank's guidance on tech; for Kadie Clark's and Michelle Popovich's strong assistant coaching and for judging. Ms. Clark still will be judging quarterfinals tomorrow. Thank you, all!

PPS. I'll post final ballot scores once we get those early next week.

Calling all Juniors (well, I guess technically you are now seniors üôÇ
We need your help decorating for Saturday's Prom. The more help we have, the faster we can get it done! We can't start decorating until 12:00pm due to the Farmer's Market at Merchant Park in the morning. Please meet at Merchant Park at noon and be prepared to work for a couple of hours. We would like to have it all done by 4:00pm so you have plenty of time to get ready for the BIG EVENT! We will also need to have juniors stay after the dance for a short time to help take down the decorations.

Please email Meagan or Summer if you have any questions.

The PHS Booster Club is excited to present the 2020 Digital Athletic Banquet Video to honor the Class of 2020. Please take the time to watch this special 38 minute video to honor our graduates!

Video Highlights Include:
Welcome - Jeff Malone
Invocation - Danielle Staats
Recognition of all Senior Athletes - Troy Maydew
Senior Athlete Message - Camdon Nickelson
Keynote Speaker - Kari Eastes
Announcement of the Judson Eisenhauer and Carter Barker Memorial Scholarships
Presentation of 2019-2020 PHS Senior Athlete Awards

This 38 minute video was produced by PHS student Troy Hamm. Thank you Troy! Also, special thanks to Elly Fowler for finding pictures for the video. Finally, please thank your Booster Club Board members for their willingness to step up to the plate and serve our students!

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0KfGSMyurNo

Congratulations to Kahrie Stegman and Colby Barradas!
Today was the National Speech and Debate Association West Kansas district awards by Zoom at 2 p.m.

Both Kahrie Stegman and Colby Barradas earned outstanding awards! Kahrie EARNED THE ACADEMIC ALL-AMERICAN for leadership and academics, one of a handful in our district to win the award. Colby Barradas will be COMPETING AT NATIONALS in DRAMATIC INTERPRETATION in mid-June, at the first virtual nationals tournament ever.

Way to Go Greenbacks!

Class of 2020.....The Cap and Gown Distribution is here. Thank you for your patience as we worked through the details with the COVID-19 pandemic.

Here is how and when we will be distributing the Jostens orders and the caps/gowns. We will do this by last names in alphabetical order.....see times below.

When: Friday May 1, 2020

Where: The front of PHS. This will be a drive by event only. PLEASE do not get out of your car. You will enter the parking lot from 5th street and get in line.

Time: 11:30 a.m A-F (last name)
12:00 noon G-N "
12:30 p.m. O-Z "

All this information was e-mailed to every senior last week.
If you have questions, please call Denise Loganbill in the PHS office at 620-672-4540.

Difficult times like the present are when the Greenback Values of Grit, Team, Valor, Passion and Respect can best demonstrated to our community and the world. So the PHS Faculty are challenging ALL Student Uncommon Greenbacks to a Video contest.

This Week the Focal Point is "VALOR" . The video best demonstrating "VALOR" will win $25 worth of Pratt Chamber Bucks. The PHS Faculty will vote to determine the winning video. Entries are due by Sunday night April 26 at midnight.

Only rules are the video has to be 3 minutes or less and social distancing rules have to be maintained unless it‚Äôs your immediate family (living under the same roof)! Also you must follow all copyright rules and regulations. This means that if you set the video to music; you must not use copyrighted music.

Again the week's focus is "VALOR" ! Get creative and show how you are practicing VALOR in your home! All Greenbacks K-12 are eligible to submit a video and to keep platforms universal please use either quick time or imovie for video submission. Please submit your videos to greenback.grit@usd382.com.

The PHS Faculty are busy this week getting ready to provide an on-line continuous learning opportunity for all PHS students Grades 9-12 starting Monday, May 30. In preparation for this, the PHS building will be open tomorrow on Wednesday, March 25 on a VERY LIMITED BASIS for students to retrieve needed personal articles out of their lockers. An E-MAIL WITH ALL DETAILS WAS SENT TO YOUR STUDENT. Please have your students read the e-mail and/or all information attached below before coming to the school.

It is very important we practice great social distancing to keep everyone safe, flatten the curve for the CO-VID-19 virus and thereby reduce the number of illness and deaths both locally and nation-wide.

post_text:
Today was the first day of the USD 382 "Grab and Go" lunches for all individuals aged 1-18, which will also include breakfast for the next morning. The USD 382 Facebook page has more details about the various pick-up sites on an earlier post.

To keep this moving forward, USD 382 Lunch Service needs to borrow 10-12 additional large coolers (preferably on wheels) for the next 8 weeks. There is not a need at this time for small coolers. If you have a cooler that can be loaned out for this period of time, please bring it by Pratt High School between the hours of 8 am - 11 am either tomorrow or Wednesday. You will need to buzz in on the west main door. To maintain social distancing, we would ask you leave it outside the main office doors. Please make sure your cooler is labeled clearly if you would like it returned. Questions - Call David Swank at 620-450-6078.

Thanks in advance for your help.
